 <purpose>
   <p>
     The Work order application module supports the requirement to 
     describe the work to be performed in response to a     
     <module_ref linkend="work_request:introduction">
       work request
     </module_ref>. 
   </p>
   <!--
   <p>
     Each work order may consist of:
     <ul>
       <li>
         a work directive (directed in response to one or more individual
         work requests);
       </li>
       <li>
         an approval status;
       </li>
       <li>
         the contract under which the work is to be undertaken;
       </li>
       <li>
         an indication of the level of completion of the work;
       </li>
       <li>
         a definition of the work to be done (the main
         activity defining the work to be completed under a work order);
       </li>
       <li>
         the product or product data (product configuration information)
         that is affected by the work directive;
       </li>
       <li>
         who is to undertake the work.
       </li>
     </ul>
   </p>
   -->

 </purpose>

 <inscope>
  <li>
    Information that describes how a request for work on a product or
    product data is addressed and carried out;
  </li>
  <li>
    the identification of the originating work request for the work to be
    carried out on a product or product data.
  </li>
 </inscope>

 <outscope>
  <li>
    The identification of the approval for the work to be carried out on a
    product or product data;
     <note number="1">
       The association of approvals to a work_order is provided by extending this module.
     </note>
  </li>
  <li>
    the identification of the contract that the work to be will be assigned to;
     <note number="2">
       The association of contract to a work_order is provided by extending this module.
     </note>
  </li>
   <li>
     the association of dates to the work_order in a particular role such
     as the date the work_order was raised;
     <note number="3">
       The association of dates to work_orders is provided by extending this module.
     </note>
   </li>
   <li>
     the association of people or organizations to the work_order on a
     given role.
     <note number="4">
       The association of a person or organization to a work_order is
       provided by extending this module. 
     </note>
   </li>
 </outscope>


